post_text:
Greetings!

I am reaching out from Homewood Science Center because we are working with Illinois Action for Children to push to educate hard-to-count neighborhoods about the Census 2020. I know your plate is probably overloaded right now with the development and transitions due to COVID-19, but it is imperative that we do everything in our power to ensure an accurate count for Illinois, and especially for hard-to-count neighborhoods.

Please take time to complete your Census 2020.

Brandi Hardin
Administrative Coordinator | Homewood Science Center
18022 Dixie Hwy | Homewood, Il, 60430
www.homewoodsciencecenter.org

Social Worker
Science Teacher
Instructional Technology
Art Teacher
Spanish Teacher
Substitute Custodians

Crossing Guards

post_text:
Is your child three or four with a birthday on or before September 1st? If so, schedule a PreK screening today. The next screening date is this Friday, October 10th. Call 708-798-0945 to make your appointment.

The purpose of this screening is to determine if your child may be at-risk for future academic difficulty. Children's development in the areas of speech, language, fine motor, gross motor, concept formation, and preschool readiness skills are screened. Results of these screenings are used to identify students who might be at risk of developing difficulties with school and to identify students for further evaluation if a disability is suspected. #hcsd1525 #preschool #earlychildhood

Parents, did you know your children can receive a FREE breakfast and lunch?
Hazel Crest School District 152¬Ω would like to invite you to our summer meal program. Community residents 18 and under are eligible for a free breakfast and lunch. This program will run until June 26, 2014.

Breakfast 8:30 a.m. - 9:00 a.m.
Lunch 11:30 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.
Monday - Thursday

For more information, please contact the school at 708.335.0224
